methods.add:
Write newData to this table.

:param newData: (io.deephaven.db.tables.Table) - the data to write to this table
methods.canEdit:
Queries whether this MutableInputTable is editable in the current context.

:return: (boolean) true if this MutableInputTable may be edited, false otherwise TODO (deephaven/deephaven-core/issues/255):
         Add AuthContext and whatever else is appropriate
methods.delete:
Delete the keys contained in the parameter table from this input table. This method will block until rows are
 deleted.

*Overload 1*  
  :param table: (io.deephaven.db.tables.Table) - The rows to delete.
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param table: (io.deephaven.db.tables.Table) - The rows to delete.
  :param index: io.deephaven.db.v2.utils.Index
methods.getDefinition:
Get the key and value columns names for this table.

:return: (io.deephaven.web.shared.data.InputTableDefinition) the InputTableDefinition.
methods.getDescription:
Return a user-readable description of this MutableInputTable.

:return: (java.lang.String) a description of this input table
methods.getKeyNames:
Get the names of the key columns

:return: (java.lang.String[]) an array with the names of our key columns
methods.getTable:
Returns a Deephaven table that contains the current data for this MutableInputTable.

:return: (io.deephaven.db.tables.Table) the current data in this MutableInputTable.
methods.getTableDefinition:
Get the underlying Table definition (which includes the names and types of all of the columns).

:return: (io.deephaven.db.tables.TableDefinition) the TableDefinition for our user-visible table
methods.hasColumn:
Returns true if the specified column exists in this MutableInputTable.

:param columnName: (java.lang.String) - the column to interrogate
:return: (boolean) true if columnName exists in this MutableInputTable
methods.isKey:
Returns true if the specified column is a key.

:param columnName: (java.lang.String) - the column to interrogate
:return: (boolean) true if columnName is a key column, false otherwise

text: A minimal interface for mutable tables that can be changed over the OpenAPI.
